args: Cleaning 101 dictates that we start\nat the top and work our way down.\nDust, then sweep.
Rgh... Remind me why\nI have to do this again?
I told you. You're going to learn what\nnormal, everyday life is like.
And right now, that means housework!\nNext, you will scrub the floors.
Ugh. This dirt won't come off.\nWait— *gasp*
This is a Syndicate cipher\ndisguised as dirt, isn't it?!
Oh, for goodness sake. Quell your\nimagination for five seconds and CLEAN!
Given your inexperience, we'll begin\nwith something simple. I'd like you to\nsimply boil these vegetables.
Hah. I'm not THAT pea-brained. Save\nthe lesson for someone who needs it.
Confident, are you?\nThen I'll observe from over here.\nGo ahead.
First, I cut the vegetables \nand put them in the pot.
Then, I fill the pot with water!
Now to crank up the heat!
(He needs to turn the burner down,\nor the pot will—)
Rrgh. I can't believe the Syndicate\nsabotaged my cooking pot!
What did I say about blaming the\nSyndicate for everything?!
It was something of a struggle at first,\nbut he's managing now.
He's stopped mentioning the Syndicate\nevery few minutes, at least.
And his growth does not stop there.\nHe seems to have a hobby now.
That's almost hard to picture.\nSo what's he into?
Say WHAT? Ain't raisin' veggies a\nlittle outta character for a hothead\nlike him?
He's quite passionate about it, to be sure.\nAnd as long as we're on the subject...
You see? Aldred tended to\nall the vegetables here.
Whoa. Never woulda expected ol'\ndanger-boy to have such a green thumb.
Well, look who's decided to join us.
'Sup, Aldred. You here ta\ngive the veggies some TLC?
I guess Cleo told you. What,\nis there some rule saying I can't?
I think it's a great hobby, Aldred.
Hah. Bet you think it doesn't suit\nme at all. Go ahead and say it.
Isn't he a shy one? If anyone is worried\nabout their actions not suiting their image,\nit's him.
Ta be fair, his life's been nothin' but \nbreak-or-be-broken so far.
I think he's startin' to understand\nthat not everyone's out to get him.
Mhm. If things stay peaceful like this,\nthen maybe he'll— Huh?!
A Syndicate surprise attack!\nYou'll regret this folly, you dastards!
M-my bad! Did anyone get hurt?!
Yeah, I was practicing and my hand\nslipped. Sorry! Are you all okay?
Criminy! Did he get hurt?\nShow me, quick!
A single arrow isn't gonna take me down.\nI'll have your head, you—
...No, wait. You fought against the\nSyndicate, too. You can't be one of them.
Heh. Right you are.\n'Preciate the trust, Aldred.
I'm just glad nobody lost an eye.\nAnd good job keepin' yer cool, Aldred.
Heck, just about anyone woulda swung\nback after that. Did ya realize somehow\nit was just Luca?
No, I didn't know who it was.\nBut right as I was about to attack...
Hm? What are you looking at?\n...Oh, I get it!
If you'd retaliated, then the\nvegetable garden would've been\ncaught in the carnage.
Heck, we'd be lookin' at a smokin' crater\ninstead of tomorrow's salad greens.
The vegetables deserved better than that.
Outstanding! It seems you're starting to\nunderstand, Aldred.
Taking good care of what you CAN observe,\nrather than detesting an invisible foe—
That is what a normal life is like.
